# Accessibility and Dark Mode

- Use adaptive colors (`.primary`, `.secondary`, system backgrounds) and verify icon contrast in dark mode.
- Ensure all icon-only controls have accessibility labels and helpful `.help(...)` where useful.
- Support Dynamic Type: avoid truncation for key actions/headlines and use `lineLimit` intentionally.
- Do not communicate status by color alone; pair color with text or icon state.
- Keep interactive controls comfortably tappable and separated to prevent accidental taps.

## Contrast Pattern

```swift
Image(systemName: available ? "checkmark" : "xmark")
    .foregroundStyle(available ? Color.white : Color.secondary)
    .accessibilityLabel(available ? "Available" : "Unavailable")
```
